    <string name="consent_title">Set up your Linux environment</string>
    <string name="consent_message">CoDebian is a developer tool that runs your own Debian Linux
        environment and the code-server editor entirely on this device.\n\nTo do this, it will:
        \n\n\u2022 Download a standard Debian (trixie) userspace image from Docker Hub\n\u2022 Run
        it in an unprivileged, app-sandboxed container (via proot) -- no root required\n\u2022
        Install and start code-server, bound only to 127.0.0.1 on this device (never exposed on
        your network)\n\nNothing you do inside this Linux environment changes CoDebian\'s own app
        code -- it only affects files inside your private sandbox, which you fully control and can
        reset at any time. No data leaves your device.\n\nThis download happens once and requires
        network access.</string>
    <string name="consent_accept">Set Up Linux Environment</string>
    <string name="consent_decline">Not Now</string>
    <string name="consent_declined_message">CoDebian needs your consent to download and run the
        Linux environment before it can start.</string>
